item.title: About
item.description: I’m Felicia. I currently conduct human-computer interaction research at the National University of Singapore (NUS-HCI lab), and previously worked with tech startups and VC. I’m plagued by insatiable intellectual hunger and entrepreneurial spirit, though I’d rather describe myself as a quiet artist at heart. Music and depth psychology are the two main portals by which I access my interior experience, and the collective human psyche. I’m too fond of my strings (guitar, violin), the ocean, Carl Jung and all things soulful.
